ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

You ask your parents or another family member for a loan to help you through a difficult financial time. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your family member would want to help you?
You ask your parents or other family members
You approach a close friend to talk after doing or saying something that seriously upset him/her. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your friend would want to talk to you?
You approach a close friend to talk after doing or saying something that seriously upset him/her. You would expect that he/she would want to talk with you to try to work things out.
You bring up the issue of sexual protection with your significant other and tell him/her how important you think it is. How concerned or anxious would you be over his/her reaction?

You bring up the issue of sexual protection with your significant other and tell him/her how important you think it is. You would expect that he/she would be willing to discuss your possible options without getting defensive.
You ask your supervisor for help with a problem you have been having at work. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to help you?
You ask your supervisor for help with a problem you have been having at work. You would expect that he/she would want to help you out.

After a bitter argument, you call or approach your significant other because you want to make up. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your significant other would want to make up with you?
After a bitter argument, you call or approach your significant other because you want to make up. You would expect that he/she would be at least as eager to make up as you would be.
You ask your partner or other family members to come to an occasion that's important to you. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not they would want to come?
You ask your partner or other family members to come to an occasion that's important to you. You would expect that they would want to come.

At a party, you notice someone on the other side of the room that you'd like to get to know, and you approach him or her to try to start a conversation. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to talk with you?

At a party, you notice someone on the other side of the room that you'd like to get to know, and you approach him or her to try to start a conversation. You would expect that he/she would want to talk with you.

Lately you've been noticing some distance between yourself and your significant other, and you ask him/her if there is something wrong. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not he/she still loves you and wants to be with you?

Lately you've been noticing some distance between yourself and your significant other, and you ask him/her if there is something wrong. You would expect that he/she will show sincere love and commitment to your relationship no matter what else may be going on.
You call a friend when there is something on your mind that you feel you really need to talk about. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your friend would want to listen?
You call a friend when there is something on your mind that you feel you really need to talk about.  You would expect that he/she would listen and support you.

You ask a friend to do you a big favor. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your friend would do this favor?
You ask a friend to do you a big favor. I would expect that he/she would willingly do this favor for me.

You go to a party and notice someone on the other side of the room and then you ask him/her to dance. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to dance with you?
You go to a party and notice someone on the other side of the room and then you ask him/her to dance. I would expect that he/she would want to dance with me.

You ask someone in class if you can borrow his/her notes. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to lend you his/her notes?
I would expect that the person would willingly give me his/her class notes if I asked to borrow them.
You ask your boyfriend/girlfriend to move in with you. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to move in with you?
I would expect that he/she would want to move in with me, if I asked my boyfriend/girlfriend to do so.
You ask your parents for help in deciding what programs to apply to. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want to help you?
I would expect that they would want to help me if I asked my parents for help in deciding what programs to apply to.
You ask someone you don't know well out on a date. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not the person would want to go out with you?
I would expect that the person would want to go out with me if I asked someone I didn't know well to go out on a date.

Your boyfriend/girlfriend has plans to go out with friends tonight, but you really want to
spend the evening with him/her, and you tell him/her so. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your boyfriend/girlfriend would decide to stay in?
I would expect that the person would willingly choose to stay in, if I asked my boyfriend/girlfriend to stay in with me rather than go out with his/her friends.
You ask your parents for extra money to cover living expenses. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would help you out?
I would expect that my parents would not mind helping me out to cover living expenses.

After class, you tell your professor that you have been having some trouble with a section of the course and ask if he/she can give you some extra help. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your professor would want to help you out?
I would expect that my professor would want to help me out if I asked for extra help with a certain section of the course materials.
How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want you to come home?
I would expect I would be welcome at home with my parents.
After graduation, you can't find a job and ask your parents if you can live at home for a while. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want you to come home?
I would expect I would be welcome at home if I could not find a job after graduation and asked to move back in with my parents.
You ask your parents to come to an occasion important to you. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your parents would want to come?
I would expect that my parents would want to come if I asked them to come to an occasion important to me.
You ask your boyfriend/girlfriend if he/she really loves you. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your boyfriend/girlfriend would say yes?
I would expect that he/she would answer yes sincerely if I asked my boyfriend/girlfriend if he/she really loved me.
You ask your boyfriend/girlfriend to come home to meet your parents. How concerned or anxious would you be over whether or not your boyfriend/girlfriend would want to meet your parents?
I would expect that my boyfriend/girlfriend would want to meet my parents if I asked him/her to come to meet them.
